The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Saturday, May 03, 2003 				 ACC posts lower net at Rs 121 cr
 OUR BUREAU																								Mumbai, May 2: Associated Cement Companies Ltd (ACC) has posted a lower net profit of Rs 121.34 crore on a consolidated basis in 2002-03 compared with Rs 127.25 crore posted during the same period a year ago.																								The companys board has recommended a dividend of Rs 2.50 per share for the financial year, ACC said in a release here today. 																								ACCs net sales on a consolidated basis stood at Rs 3,534.74 crore during the period compared with Rs 3,268.70 crore posted in 2001-02. On a standalone basis, ACC posted a lower net profit at Rs 103.89 crore during the fiscal compared with Rs 130.43 crore recorded a year ago.																								ACCs total income (net of excise) rose to Rs 2,988.51 crore during the fiscal as against Rs 2,904.51 crore posted during the same period a year ago, it added.																								The company posted a 11.8 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 58.72 crore in the fourth quarter. 
